content:
brundi, why no response to ICE's accusation? <br>
<br>
@pine: you do realize that ICE was commenting on brundi, not on jee?

@ICE Mind addressing my question on page one, re:semi-serious vote? Or directing to where you've answered it in case I missed that.<br>
<br>
Also I took note of your comment on Michel, re:trustworthiness, but found your own admission of playing terrible scum and being an easy to read player interesting. Are we to take that as a pro-town nod to yourself?<br>
<br>
@AurorusVox I'm not sure if you're expecting me to address your vote since you seem to have confused the difference between content to comment on and content to vote on. I've done the former, not the latter. You've made it clear that you hate RVS and have voted a damned dirty random voter accordingly, but are you going to comment on the content thus far? Apparently there's enough of it, so is there anything you wish to bring to everyone's attention?

Your non-random vote has landed on a player I'm getting a mild townread on, pine. Not liking your vote, not liking your lack of content throughout these first 3 pages. There's scumpotential there.<br>
<br>
@SV: I like the way your thoughts are going. What's your opinion on Alduskel pressuring pine for not answering nhammen's question?

@jee: do you believe scum is more likely to be defensive then town is? Why?<br>
<br>
<blockquote><div><cite>pecan wrote:</cite>Alduskkel appears to have gotten lazy already, but why the votes on him?</div></blockquote>For instructing pine to spend time away from the game when pine indicated he wasn't willing to do so. Could be scum coaching or scum trying to prevent scumhunting. From town, I would have expected more questioning of motives rather then direct instructions.<br>
<br>
@Arugula: I don't really understand #109. It seems to me that you did notice jee's vote ("his recent quag vote seemed genuine") but then forgot about it ("but he didn't vote him").

@PoPP I suppose semantics aren't *hugely* important, but I'm just always careful about how people word things.<br>
<br>
This has definitely been some interesting activity, and I apologize for not being as active. All the good stuff seems to happen when I'm asleep. Will post more after seeing if a CC comes.

@Arugula: should you flip town, quidagis' opinion on you in his list of all players can be analysed. It put you as pro-town with virtually no argument. I don't know which direction the analysis would go, but that's where I would look.<br>
<br>
@ICE: With some scumtells, info to be gained from the lynch and no better alternatives, I think I would indeed hammer him in that scenario. I feel I've gotten a reasonable read on all players in the game, so I wouldn't need to hold off on hammering to allow for more discussion. I might give some advance warning though, to give others the opportunity to finish up their discussion as well.<br>
<br>
Lack of time, so short post.

@AV: Had you taken a look at anything that happened recently, or did you just start reading at page 5 and posted your thoughts as you went along?<br>
<br>
@Brundibar: you really shouldn't have ignored my #245. With deadline looming, we need people to take responsibility for their votes.<br>
<br>
@Arugula: who do you think is the best lynch for today, and why aren't you voting him or her? Surely you must feel that there are better lynches then yourself?

@ms, I ISO'd myself, and read from my last post onwards. I was on my phone so I read each page then posted whatever had interested me on it before going on the next one.<br>
<br>
I support a hammer.

@AV: I dont' want to lynch ICE today.<br>
<br>
@Whiskers: the last paragraph of <a href="https://forum.mafiascum.net/viewtopic.php?p=4101511#p4101511" class="postlink">post #151</a> is the post where I first notice the connection between Arugula and your playerslot. Both Arugula and Quidagis gave opinions on all players, and in both lists, the opinion on the other stood out.<br>
<br>
@Arugula: I believe your flip is going to give us valuable information. If you flip scum, then Whiskers and nhammen come into the picture, because of the connection and the way they are defending you. If you flip town, AV does become more suspicious for the way he originally moved onto your wagon.

@Pine, because he's now confirmed town. And we have found confirmed scum.<br>
<br>
Why on EARTH would I support an Arugulu lynch in these circumstances?

The reason I'm more suspicious of a tracker claim when we know there's a doublevoter in the game, is simple. Doublevoters are relatively rare. When a mod decides to use one in their game, they are likely to design the setup with the presence of the doublevoter in mind. As pine mentioned, tracker and doublevoter do not interact in any meaningful way. This makes it less interesting for the mod to add both a tracker and a doublevoter to the same game. Add a cop to the mix, and things become completely unbelievable. As whiskers also explained.<br>
<br>
@Aurorus, CES: I prefer a pine lynch over an ICE lynch at the moment, because connections to pine do play a part in my case against ICE, but not the other way around. Also, unlikely claim by pine. You both list ICE and pine among your suspects. Why do you think an ICE lynch is better then a pine lynch, exactly?

@all:<br>
<br>
Maybe we should list our suspects and go from there. You know my two right now, what are everyone else's.
